snippet.textDisplay: #2 Gobekli Tepi -- great find! But it would make far more sense if researchers would just admit that their "dating" was off.  As long as people aren't too upset by a given "date," they're usually not challenged, but there have been cases where rival theories have lead to one group using a different technique or different samples, and -- surprise, surprise -- they got a very different "date"!  You might look up the case where researchers thought they had found 40,000-year-old human footprints in Mexico -- it didn't fit the standard story, so another group tried getting a date for them ... and it came out over 1 million years old! Turned out to all be over nothing -- further analysis lead to the conclusion the prints weren't footprints at all!
